# Plan Review: GitHub Multi-Repository Migration v1

Date: 2026-07-11
Reviewer: Codex plan review

## Findings

- The plan matches the approved design: public repositories, component-first push ordering, submodule registration, and safe handling of the dirty original checkout.
- Every remote mutation is preceded by a local-state or target-state check.
- No force-push or recursive deletion is prescribed.
- Optional PyPI publication, original-repository archiving, team notification, and temporary-work-copy deletion are explicitly deferred.
- The final verification covers local repository state, submodule gitlinks, available local builds/tests, and GitHub Actions status.

## Verdict

Result: APPROVED
